						<h2>Instantiating a Variable</h2>
						<p>After we have declared the variable, we can then assign it a value. A variable can be assigned any value provided that it is of the same type. 
							<ul>
								<li>Integers are specified as digits. For example: int x = 5; </li>
								<li>Floats are specified as decimals or just integers. For example: float x = 3.5;</li>
								<li>Characters are specified using single quotes: char c = 'h'; </li>
								<li>String are specified in double quotes. For example: char s[30] = "hello there";</li>
							</ul>
						</p>
